Genitalia. Scale bars: 0.5 mm in A; 0.3 mm in B; 0.2 mm in C, D, F, G; 0.05 mm in E, 0.1 mm in H.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="58.[151,1437,1495,1845]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis box="[199,283,1495,1521]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Female</emphasis>
. Similar to male in external morphology; antenna shorter; each compound eye composed of approximately 18 ommatidia; humeral angle rounded; legs and abdomen lacking modifications. Measurements (as for male): body length 
<quantity box="[371,537,1567,1593]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.935" metricValueMax="1.97" metricValueMin="1.9" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" unit="mm" value="1.935" valueMax="1.97" valueMin="1.9">1.90–1.97 mm</quantity>
; length/width of head 0.39–0.41/ 
<quantity box="[909,1010,1567,1593]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.1" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" unit="mm" value="0.41">0.41 mm</quantity>
, pronotum 0.42–0.43/ 
<quantity box="[1259,1361,1567,1593]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.3" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" unit="mm" value="0.43">0.43 mm</quantity>
, elytra 0.59/ 
<quantity box="[208,373,1602,1629]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.25" metricValueMax="7.3" metricValueMin="7.199999999999999" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" unit="mm" value="0.725" valueMax="0.73" valueMin="0.72">0.72–0.73 mm</quantity>
; abdomen 0.53–0.62/ 
<quantity box="[612,776,1602,1629]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.8500000000000005" metricValueMax="6.8999999999999995" metricValueMin="6.800000000000001" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" unit="mm" value="0.685" valueMax="0.69" valueMin="0.68">0.68–0.69 mm</quantity>
; length of antenna 
<quantity box="[985,1150,1603,1629]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.05" metricValueMax="8.1" metricValueMin="8.0" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" unit="mm" value="0.805" valueMax="0.81" valueMin="0.8">0.80–0.81 mm</quantity>
; maximum width of genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[215,317,1639,1665]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="58.[151,250,1352,1376]" captionTargetBox="[160,1436,182,1326]" captionTargetId="figure-19@58.[151,1436,181,1328]" captionTargetPageId="58" captionText="FIGURE 24. Morphology of Arthromelodes songxiaobini sp. nov. (A–G. Male. H. Female). A. Dorsal habitus. B. Head and pronotum. C. Mesotibia. D. Tergites 4 and 5 (VII and VIII). E. Sternite 7 (IX). F, G. Aedeagus, lateral (F) and ventral (G). H. Genitalia. Scale bars: 0.5 mm in A; 0.3 mm in B; 0.2 mm in C, D, F, G; 0.05 mm in E, 0.1 mm in H." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6340787" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6340787/files/figure.png" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Fig. 24H</figureCitation>
) 
<quantity box="[332,435,1639,1665]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.6" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" unit="mm" value="0.26">0.26 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="58.[151,1437,1495,1845]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,434,1674,1701]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Comparative notes.</emphasis>
The mesally expanded mesotibiae of the male of the new species is shared only with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yin" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Arthromelodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nomurai">
<emphasis box="[1412,1429,1675,1701]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[151,246,1711,1736]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">nomurai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. These two species can be readily separated by the medially concave male tergite 5 (VIII) and the characteristic form of the aedeagus of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yin" authorityYear="2022" box="[507,683,1747,1773]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Arthromelodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="songxiaobini">
<emphasis box="[507,524,1747,1773]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[538,683,1747,1773]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">songxiaobini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
